# Sovereign Data Continuity Protocol v7.0 – Final Forensically-Ready Edition
Date: 19 November 2025  
Owner: Andy Jones

> This is the single document for a court-appointed digital-forensics examiner, a CISO performing due diligence, or a successor custodian. Concise, complete, non-promotional.

---
## 1. System Overview (Workflow)
```
[Off-site VeraCrypt SSD] ← monthly rotation ← [Golden Master SSD (SSD2TB)]
                                                          ↓
                                                    PC-4 (static IP)
                                                          ↓ SMB share
        5 Windows PCs + TerraMaster NAS  ← daily 04:00 ←  /MIR + git verify
                                                          ↓
                                      Encrypted remotes (git-remote-gcrypt)
```

## 2. Golden Master
- Device: 2 TB external SSD (serial: [appendix])
- Host: PC-4
- Path: `E:\COLDSTORE-SOVEREIGN-2025-11-19`
- Type: Git repository (mandatory GPG-signed commits & tags)

## 3. GPG Signing (Enforced)
```bash
git config --local commit.gpgsign true
git config --local tag.gpgsign true
git config --local user.signingkey <KEYID>
```
All commits and tags are signed. Verification mandatory on pull/sync.

## 4. Git Rebase Advanced Techniques
| Technique | Command | Use Case |
|-----------|---------|----------|
| Refresh branch | `git fetch; git rebase origin/main` | Bring dev up to date |
| Interactive cleanup | `git rebase -i origin/main` | Squash / reorder / edit |
| Autosquash fixups | `git commit --fixup=<sha>` → `git rebase -i --autosquash` | Clean history automatically |
| Move branch base | `git rebase --onto main <old> dev` | Transplant feature |
| Preserve merges | `git rebase --rebase-merges origin/main` | Retain meaningful merges |
| Test during rebase | `git rebase -i --exec "npm test"` | CI-style gate |
| Abort & recover | `git rebase --abort` / `git reflog + git reset --hard <ref>` | Safe rollback |

Rule: **Never rebase `main` except via the nightly PC-4 promotion script.**

## 5. Daily Operations
- Work only on `dev` branch (all devices).  
- Nightly promotion to `main` (PC-4, 03:55) – rebase + signed tag.  
- Daily mirror (04:00) – `robocopy /MIR` + `git verify-commit` on all endpoints.

## 6. Encrypted Remotes (git-remote-gcrypt)
```bash
git remote add nas-crypt gcrypt::/volume1/Encrypted/Sovereign.git
git remote add offsite-crypt gcrypt::file:///F/Sovereign-Encrypted.git
```
Monthly push from PC-4 only.

## 7. Threat Model & Residual Risk
| Threat | Mitigation | Residual |
|--------|------------|----------|
| Hardware failure | Multi-device mirror + monthly off-site SSD | Very Low |
| Ransomware | Offline master + one-way sync + GPG verification | Near Zero |
| Theft / environmental | Off-site VeraCrypt SSD + gcrypt remote | Low |
| Tampering | GPG-signed history + SHA-256 manifest | Near Zero |
| Accidental deletion | Nightly authoritative mirror | Very Low |
| Key compromise | Revocation certificate prepared | Low |

## 8. Digital Forensics Tool Alignment
- **Autopsy / Sleuth Kit:** Ingest SHA-256 manifest; validate file set.  
- **EnCase / FTK:** Treat GPG-signed Git history as chain-of-custody timeline.  
- **X-Ways Forensics:** Mount VeraCrypt volume read-only; correlate tags to snapshot chronology.

